<span> The European Union reaffirmed this Friday, on the occasion of the International Day against Homophobia, Transphobia and Biphobia (IDAHOBIT), its commitment "for a Europe in which everyone is free to love and live without fear". </span
<br> "We reaffirm our commitment to a Europe in which everyone is free to love and live without fear. Where you can just be yourself. Today and every day I am proud to support the LGBTIQ+ community," said the President of the European Commission Ursula von der Leyen on social network X.
